Package: ExtendedPheWAS
Type: Package
Title: Extended Phenome Wide Association Studies with Multi-Vocabulary Support
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Rob", "Howles", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "rob.howles@example.com"))
Description: Extends PheWAS to support ICD-9, ICD-10, OPCS-3, OPCS-4, Read
    codes v2, Read codes v3, and SNOMED-CT. Provides automated NLP-based mapping
    of surgical procedure codes to phenotype codes (phecodes), including new
    procedure phecodes in the 1000+ range. Supports the full PheWAS analysis
    pipeline including phenotype creation, association testing, and Manhattan
    plot visualization across all supported vocabularies.
License: GPL-3
Depends:
    R (>= 4.0.0),
    PheWAS
Imports:
    ggplot2 (>= 3.0.0),
    grDevices,
    rlang,
    stats,
    utils
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    ggrepel,
    DT
Remotes:
    PheWAS/PheWAS
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Config/testthat/edition: 3
